10/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- On Wednesday (10 September), President Stipe Mesic began the first official visit to Belgrade by a Croatian head of state since the breakup of Yugoslavia.He is due to meet Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic, Parliamentary Speaker Dragoljub Micunovic and Montenegrin officials. A spokeswoman for Mesic said not all problems between the two countries would be tackled during the one-day trip; however, she added, the visit is expected to spur further negotiations, particularly concerning the return of Serb refugees from the 1991-1995 war. The leaders are also expected to discuss regional co-operation and prospects for membership in the EU and NATO. (HINA, BBC - 10/09/03; Tanjug AFP - 09/09/03)
